    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-05T10:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-05T10:40:00-05:00" n="216"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d216">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1178.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Sullivan</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-05T11:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 5, 1914, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your December 31, 5 p.m. Total amount of immediate pressing worthy claims
                    approximately $741,800. Total amount back salaries from June to October
                    $386,535. Mailing itemized statement memorials and recommendations as
                    instructed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
